The evidence with the title 'My child ate a cigarette! ' says The amount in only one cigarette butt is enough to poison a child.  ... Poisonous: cigarettes, cigars, chewing tobacco, pipe tobacco, nicotine gum if chewed by a child, nicotine patches if chewed on by a child, and liquid nicotine used for electronic cigarettes.  ... The most commonly poisoned children are 6 years old or younger. 
